snippet.title: Art
snippet.description:
Great art should challenge our perception of the world and of ourselves - even, yes, challenge our perception of what art can be. It is the essence of the human spirit, a emotional snapshot in time that a camera could not possibly replicate. It's what separates us from savages, keeps us questioning the order of things all the way up to our place in the universe. It is also a dick-knob in a purple shirt.

snippet.title: The Fall
snippet.description: It was just his luck: The Stair-Gun Killer, a notorious mass murderer whose crimes involved taping guns to stairs and hooking up tripwires to the triggers, had begun a new cycle of deaths in the tri-county area. But there was the tricky question of the motive: Why would SGK want to kill a simple cat burglar, when most of his victims were small dogs and the ankles of children? The numbers did not add up. Later that day, after saying all of this to himself in the car, Detective McClanahan shaved his dick hair, changed his name and skipped town.

snippet.description:
Our Kickstarter! http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/5sf/dude-bro-party-massacre-3?ref=card

Our Updates!
1. Everyone who HAS contributed $5 or WILL contribute $5 gets a DRM-free digital download of "5sf: Year One!" Take a comprehensive trip back in time to when we were just starting out, including our formative college years!

snippet.title: Harry's Ex-Wives
snippet.description: Sometimes, you honestly think they invented the word "Divorce" just for Harry. Of course, they didn't, but they did invent another word for Harry: "Winchbuck," which Webster's determined to mean "a sexually unsatisfied, self-loathing sociopath who would push his/her own mother off a cliff if it meant getting laid." The word enjoyed a brief fling with relevancy in the early 10's until someone took it too far and actually pushed their mom off a cliff. Now we never speak of Winchbuck again.

snippet.title: Door-to-Door Door Salesman
snippet.description:
9 times outta 10, the customer says no. It's a tough racket, being a salesman. But what keeps people coming back to this job is that 1 time out of 10, when there's a need to be satiated, and only the sweet cherry-finish gleam of your new H-series model will do. When there's a pounding in their head, an aching for something better, and you drown in out with the robust hearty knock of your Seabreeze Type 5 Unit. Yes, those are the glory days when a sale is made, and you never know when opportunity will come a-knockin'. So we keep on a-walkin'.

snippet.title: Manbortion
snippet.description: You ever passed a kidney stone, son? (Hunkers down, pours six grams of Bushmills in an iced tumbler, lights a Cohiba and exhales) No, I imagine not. You still got a sparkle in your eye. So take the greatest pain a man can feel, short of losing his woman to the war, and multiply it by about a thousand. Give that stone some eyes and teeth, a heart and a soul, and now you got yourself a little question: Spend $235K to raise it, or $10,000 to repair the shredded, bleeding balloon you got for a pecker?
